It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. It's the last room in the house that was only given a simple decoration.
Tear down the ugly electric wall heater and the fireplace bed. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Customize a wardrobe.
Usually, we start by drawing a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
Several dead birds were found behind the flue, all of them dried up :(
Get ready for the plasterer next week
Very satisfied with the small niche next to it
Install the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing yet🙈)
Ha ha, look what we found behind the radiator!
Remember the cute little vent added to prevent the chimney from getting damp
Sweep has installed both the chimney cover and the chimney cap. The magpies that like to nest in the chimney should be safer now 🪺
The plasterer is done. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork underlay has been laid, and we even made an attachment for the vacuum cleaner using toilet paper rolls to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has been prepared and is ready to be laid. Let's have a cup of tea and rest a bit.
Well, today's progress was a bit slow because in order to seamlessly connect with the corridor (which is also having the floor laid), I had to do some cutting around the door frame, which was quite laborious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me all along
Finally finished, but it's a mess! Even worse, the instructions for assembling the new bed are terrible. Finally, I can have a good night's sleep tonight!
The corridor floor and baseboards are still not done. The renovation workers won't come for a month, so we can only make do for now, with just bare drywall in the room.
In the evening, I did a simple DIY, cutting off part of the bottom of the door frame with a tenon saw and chisel, so that the floor can be perfectly laid underneath.
The cork underlayment in the corridor is also laid.
Yesterday we also laid the floor in the corridor! This morning at 5 o'clock, I got up and went to Heathrow Airport to pick up package number one, then took a nap, and now finally I can start installing the baseboards in the corridor. After the adhesive dries, I will fill the gaps.
